The Sharks beat the Stormers 26-19
to advance to the Super Rugby final against the Chiefs.  Frederic Michalekâ€™s 76th-minute drop goal clinched the win
for the Sharks in the all-South African semifinal in  Cape Town .
Michalek kicked 16 points, while JP Pietersen and Louis Ludik
scored tries for the visitors.  Gio Aplon touched down and Peter Grant booted 14 points for
the Stormers, who had the No. 1 seeding in the playoffs after
topping the regular-season standings.  The Sharks will travel to Hamilton,  New Zealand , to face
the Chiefs for the title on Aug. 4. The Chiefs advanced with a
20-17 win over the Crusaders yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
